30:03.920 --> 30:14.820
I was going to start with a reference to the West Coast maneuvers of July 1941,
before the United States was officially in World War II. There were two armies,

30:15.340 --> 30:25.880
one of regular Army units and one of former National Guard outfits, with the
rules made so the regulars couldn't possibly lose. They were losing, so the

30:25.880 --> 30:35.480
rules were changed to favor them still more. And again. Finally, the whole thing
was called off a week early, just before the final debacle. You see, all during

30:35.480 --> 30:44.880
peacetime, the War College keeps the regular Army officers trained about what to
do when war comes. The National Guard officers get some of this, but they don't

30:44.880 --> 30:53.900
take it all that seriously, because they have to spend most of their time living
in the real world, something the regular officers don't know much about. There

30:53.900 --> 31:02.880
was one guy in my regiment who did take it seriously. the security officer. The
others didn't take him seriously, but they should have. He was what it was all

31:02.880 --> 31:16.660
about. Well, we're right. We do make cracks about the military in Martin. And we
don't see that much difference between military occupation troops in so-called

31:16.660 --> 31:29.900
peace and the conquest troops in war. Oh, the bodies are prettier. They shave
and bathe more often. in almost all societies the organization of fighters for

31:29.900 --> 31:40.320
war parallels that of men's work groups in fact they often have the same
personnel but in our society and I include here the Soviets the organization of

31:40.320 --> 31:50.100
the military is like the social organization which preceded ours the kind of
society we refer to as feudal or semi-feudal the peasant-based societies

31:50.100 --> 31:58.640
organized into patron-cliant sets, where patrons are to make the decisions and
clients are first to be exploited and second to be hoarded. And to put up with

31:58.640 --> 32:08.080
that, they have to be specially indoctrinated. As Auburn McDermott reminded us
from the audience at Oakland, four hundred years and more ago, the people did

32:08.080 --> 32:19.480
not think the way we did. Our type of civilian mind was then just beginning to
rise to contest the hitherto unchallenged rule of the military mind. and then I

32:19.480 --> 32:29.440
was going to ask if anyone in the audience knows the purpose of close order
drill the Russians once tried to abolish close order drill and they found that

32:29.440 --> 32:39.940
they had no army L. Ron Hubbard who wrote Fear and Typewriter in the Sky and
that masterpiece Final Blackout and Ordok Methuselah stories was in the military

32:39.940 --> 32:51.500
he was a navy commander and one of his basic teachings is that all authority
rests upon the ability to move people about physically in space. So, I was going

32:51.500 --> 33:01.800
to say, I'll put this in terms that at least the Scientologists here will be
able to understand. Close order drill is an opening procedure drill to reduce

33:01.800 --> 33:13.040
com lag between the time an order is received and the time it's carried out. So
I'll just go there, do that, stop it, do something else, go somewhere else. You

33:13.040 --> 33:21.840
see the close order drill and you see the opening procedure drill. It's simply
to condition you to take orders without stopping to think about it. The

33:21.840 --> 33:31.240
difference is that Scientology later teaches you how to make up your own orders
and give them to yourself. And the military never willingly lets you go. You

33:31.240 --> 33:42.640
wind up being a wind-up toy. Programmed to their ideas. and you start wondering
why these crazy civilians won't just bend over and do what you think they

33:42.640 --> 33:53.280
should. And that is why we make such remarks about the military mind. Now, I
could go on with this, but I'll sum it up. The purpose of the military is not to

33:53.280 --> 34:02.880
die for one's country. It's not even to make the enemy die for his country. It
is to make the enemy live for one's own country. That means to destroy the enemy

34:02.880 --> 34:12.180
as an independent organization. In other words, the purpose of the military is
conquest, which is to say, the increase of one's own client's set and its

34:12.180 --> 34:19.800
perpetuation. And if you want a course in the anthropology of peasant base,
military administered patron client societies, I'll be around.

34:23.480 --> 34:40.920
So, it occurs to me that some of the people on that panel awed me. I wasn't used
to the helpless inadequate feeling I got when I heard them on this subject. The

34:40.920 --> 34:50.140
nearest I can recall is the way I used to feel around a certain corporal soon
after I was first drafted into the U.S. Army. And since it's an example that

34:50.140 --> 35:04.320
shows the nature of some aspects of this particular military mind, let me tell
you. He was a little big for his age So he lied about his years and joined the

35:04.320 --> 35:14.820
National Guard when he was in high school And they double-crossed him and
started getting ready for war His outfit had been activated in October 1940 So

35:14.820 --> 35:25.860
by the time I was drafted in February 1941 He already had four months of a
nasty, muddy Puget Sound winter under his bed They'd gotten some training

35:25.860 --> 35:37.280
between raindrops and now they were a training cadre and he was a corporal and
they were supposed to pass what they'd found on gas. Well, nothing's perfect so

35:37.280 --> 35:46.700
now and then I'd have to ask a question and even very seldom make a suggestion
like, if we're going to be digging all these holes wouldn't it make sense first

35:46.700 --> 35:54.420
to set aside the turf from where the hole and the pile of dirt are going to be
and then afterward lay it over the dirt so it won't be quite so obvious just

35:54.420 --> 36:03.980
where the holes are? You know, I wasn't trying to show up to the trainers. It's
just that I wanted my fellow draftees to have at least a minimum chance of

36:03.980 --> 36:13.980
survival if it came to that. Besides, I'm selfish, and the more survivor types I
have around me, the better chance I have of surviving among them. Well, this

36:13.980 --> 36:21.380
corporal was one of the snottiest of snot-willed kids. You understand, he wasn't
dumb. He really had great potential. It's just that he thought he was already

36:21.380 --> 36:30.300
there. He was on the same floor of the same barracks as the squad I was in.
Thank God he wasn't my corporal. I had a real good corporal. I really loved

36:30.300 --> 36:42.040
having that. But the kid embarked on a real deliberate campaign to humiliate me.
Well, I was living it. Only one day I was over in the rec room writing a letter.

36:43.000 --> 36:50.840
Naturally, I got a table as far back as possible along one wall so I could see
everything, especially who came in and went out the door. Then a bunch of kids

36:50.840 --> 36:57.840
came in, including the corporals. They had an older sergeant with me. He was
from another outfit, and I'd never seen him before, but I noticed they held him

36:57.840 --> 37:07.860
in very hard regard, and he had a forest green braid on his sleeve, which meant
that in a previous military incarnation he'd been an officer. They took seats in

37:07.860 --> 37:16.060
the corner behind me, and I wasn't paying any attention, after all it was none
of my goodness, but suddenly the corporal's voice rose above the level of the

37:16.060 --> 37:30.220
conversation, and he said, The worst kind of bullet is ricochet. Ricochet. You
know. Whang! Well, I don't know what possessed me to butt in, but I turned

37:30.220 --> 37:40.540
around and said, The worst kind of bullet is a spent bullet. It drifts along.
Hunting. The sergeant got very excited. He said, You've been in action. Where

37:40.540 --> 37:51.060
were you? And I said, Hmm? You were in action. Where was it? And just about the
time I began to get back control of my lower jaw, the corporal began to realize

37:51.060 --> 37:52.880
what was happening, and he lost control of his.

37:55.820 --> 38:04.060
Well, I wish I could say that after that he was a changed character, but he
wasn't. It's just that he was no longer carrying on a deliberate campaign. But

38:04.060 --> 38:13.300
you see what I mean about a hopeless, helpless inadequacy. How do you educate
brilliant but ignorant people who already know everything? Now I want you to

38:13.300 --> 38:22.160
understand though That the corporal's attitude Was completely characteristic of
the military mind And it's documented by numerous studies Of patron client

38:22.160 --> 38:32.000
societies It's especially found in situations Where the respective ranks Do not
very much differ People who are clearly of patron grade Have much more effective

38:32.000 --> 38:41.780
ways To keep clients aware of the fact People with just a little authority Have
to keep fighting for it and the methods they use are born of desperation. The

38:41.780 --> 38:51.440
fact that I didn't want his job was immaterial. I was obviously going to be one
of the first new TFCs, and he was the youngest old corporal. To the militarized

38:51.440 --> 38:53.420
mind, he was in dire danger.

38:58.520 --> 39:09.140
